    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>GUILTY PLEA IN VIDEO PIRACY</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elsa Brenner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bernard Scheman pleads guity to criminal possession of forgery devices in operating lab in basement of video store in Mount Kisco, NY, that produced counterfeit videotapes of major movies (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Bernard Scheman, 48, of Fort Montgomery, has pleaded guilty in Westchester County Court in White Plains to criminal possession of forgery devices in operating a lab in the basement of a video store in Mount Kisco that produced counterfeit videotapes of major movies. More than 4,900 counterfeit videotapes were seized from the store in March.  Mr. Scheman and Frank Adrissone, 52, of Mount Kisco, were accused of  operating the lab in the basement of Crossroads Video, which Mr. Ardrissone owns.</p>
        <p>Elsa Brenner</p>
      </block>
